Restaurant Inspections in Queens (2011-2017)

column

Chart A: Number of code violations registered per restaturant

The average number of code violations for each restaurant remained below five at each year. However, during the later years, there were some restaurants who received large number of inspections during the year.

Chart B: Critical and Non-critical Violations

In the 7 years, restaurants have had a comparable number of both critical and non-critical violations. However, in most cases, they seem to have lot more critical violations registered than the non-critical ones. Missing values are those who either only have critical or only non-critical violations.

Column

Chart C: Is there an association between number of inspections and violation score (2014_2017)?

In the later years, cuisines whose restaurants were found to violate more/critical City and State food safety requirements also received more inspections during the year. Many of the inspections could be follow-ups. Similarly, it could also be that restuarants who are inspected more are likely to have more violations recorded.
